♪ I don't wanna wait in vain for your love ♪

24:17.247 --> 24:22.412
♪ I don't wanna wait in vain for your love ♪

24:23.003 --> 24:26.166
♪ 'Cause summer is here ♪

24:26.256 --> 24:29.669
- ♪ And I'm still waiting there ♪
- ♪ Summer is here ♪

24:29.677 --> 24:38.642
♪ Winter is here, I'm still waiting there ♪

24:45.484 --> 24:47.395
♪ Like I said ♪

24:48.445 --> 24:52.688
♪ It's been three years
since I'm knocking on your door ♪

24:54.118 --> 24:57.076
♪ And I still can knock some more ♪

24:59.248 --> 25:02.456
♪ Ooh, boy, ooh, boy ♪

25:02.459 --> 25:05.667
♪ Is it crazy?
Look, I wanna know now ♪

25:06.463 --> 25:08.704
♪ For I to knock some more ♪

25:09.466 --> 25:10.797
♪ You see ♪

25:12.052 --> 25:13.883
♪ In life I know ♪

25:13.971 --> 25:16.087
You got to say yes first.

25:18.267 --> 25:21.225
♪ But your love is my relief ♪

25:23.147 --> 25:28.483
♪ Tears in my eyes burn ♪

25:28.485 --> 25:29.349
Yes.

25:29.361 --> 25:33.070
♪ While I'm waiting,
while I'm waiting for my day ♪

25:33.323 --> 25:34.733
♪ You see ♪

25:45.252 --> 25:46.162
Wait a second.

25:46.503 --> 25:47.333
Ow.

25:48.255 --> 25:49.244
- Let me...
- I got it. I got it. I got it.

25:49.256 --> 25:50.166
- Ow, ow, ow.
- I got it.

25:50.174 --> 25:51.163
- I got it.
- Ow.

25:51.300 --> 25:52.164
Ow!

25:54.386 --> 25:56.001
Okay, you're not gonna
read into this, right, Sara?

25:56.013 --> 25:57.969
I mean, it's just an accident, nothing more.

25:57.973 --> 26:00.510
No. God, we'll get it refitted.

26:01.018 --> 26:03.634
It's beautiful. I love it.

26:03.729 --> 26:06.061
You... You get changed.
I wanna call Ryan,

26:06.065 --> 26:07.145
tell him you said yes.

26:07.274 --> 26:08.480
Why? Was he worried?

26:08.484 --> 26:09.690
Not about you.

26:09.693 --> 26:10.933
About the tour.

26:10.944 --> 26:13.185
He's hoping to fit the honeymoon
into the schedule.

26:14.948 --> 26:16.438
How's Bora Bora sound?

26:17.826 --> 26:20.408
Very... sexy sexy?

26:23.248 --> 26:28.788
♪ I don't wanna wait in vain for your love ♪

26:29.421 --> 26:34.757
♪ I don't wanna wait in vain for your love ♪

26:35.302 --> 26:37.463
♪ I don't wanna wait... ♪

26:37.471 --> 26:38.711
- Now, if you're a golfer

26:38.722 --> 26:41.134
on a one-hour lunch break,
you'd use that time up

26:41.141 --> 26:43.302
just getting to the nearest course
out of Manhattan.

26:43.977 --> 26:46.218
All this was a long overdue solution.

26:46.396 --> 26:49.684
Formerly a dilapidated pier
and converted just five years ago,

26:49.775 --> 26:52.608
the range offers the inhabitants
of this concrete jungle

26:52.611 --> 26:54.021
the chance to keep their drives straight,

26:54.029 --> 26:55.860
their short games accurate,

26:55.864 --> 26:59.277
and most of all, brings the joys
and frustrations of golf

26:59.284 --> 27:00.364
back to city folk.

27:00.744 --> 27:04.908
This is Nick Roberts, ESPN News, New York City.

27:04.915 --> 27:06.871
Superb, Nick.
We got it. Thank you.

27:07.543 --> 27:10.080
- Artie, gotta run, okay?
- What about the B-roll shot?

27:10.087 --> 27:11.827
- Paging Sara Lawson.
- No time. Totally jammed with the wedding.

27:12.005 --> 27:13.870
Paging Sara Lawson.
Please come to the front desk.

27:13.882 --> 27:15.292
You come back,
get the B-roll on Friday?

27:15.300 --> 27:17.006
- Yeah. Whatever you say, boss.
- Thank you, sir.

27:17.010 --> 27:19.251
I'm Sara Lawson. Hi.

27:19.263 --> 27:20.924
- How are you?
- Sorry I'm late.

27:20.931 --> 27:22.421
You're down at position number two.

27:22.432 --> 27:24.138
Oh, right. Bad golfers
all the way down there, right?

27:24.143 --> 27:25.849
Dude, take off. We got it.

27:31.775 --> 27:34.642
♪ Well, well, these days... ♪

27:34.653 --> 27:36.769
Well, hello,
Mr. Marrying Man.

27:37.698 --> 27:40.531
- Hi. Uh, where's Lauren?
- Oh, Lauren took the day off.

27:40.534 --> 27:42.820
My name is Sara
and I'm gonna cut your hair today.

27:44.621 --> 27:45.610
You know what?

27:45.622 --> 27:47.829
I'm not thrilled with having
that "just cut hair" look

27:47.833 --> 27:49.824
- for my own wedding, so...
- I'm just gonna take a little bit off.

27:49.835 --> 27:51.291
I gotta live with these pictures
the rest of my life.

27:51.295 --> 27:52.501
- Just a little bit.
- Please, you know, uh...

27:52.504 --> 27:53.914
♪ It's you ♪

27:54.464 --> 27:58.878
♪ And me forever, ah-ah ♪

27:58.886 --> 27:59.841
♪ Sara ♪

28:00.596 --> 28:04.180
♪ Smile ♪

28:04.183 --> 28:05.343
Whoo!

28:05.350 --> 28:08.638
- ♪ Won't you smile awhile for me? ♪
- Forget Charles Street.

28:08.645 --> 28:11.352
Take me to the <i>New York Times</i> building
on 42nd, please.

28:11.356 --> 28:12.971
- Mm-hmm.
- ♪ Sara ♪

28:14.109 --> 28:16.145
- Whoo!

28:16.612 --> 28:18.227
I'm telling you, I keep running into it.

28:18.238 --> 28:19.819
I keep finding it.
It keeps happening.

28:19.823 --> 28:21.233
She was at the golf range.

28:21.241 --> 28:23.106
She's a big girl now with big hips.
All right?

28:23.118 --> 28:26.235
Then I gotta leave
'cause Sara's gonna cut my hair,

28:26.246 --> 28:28.703
and the guy in the taxi,
he's serenading me, <i>Sara.</i>

28:28.707 --> 28:31.198
I'm telling you, the universe
keeps revealing her to me,

28:31.210 --> 28:32.620
screwing with my head.

28:32.628 --> 28:34.960
- You're getting married in three days.
- That's my point.

28:34.963 --> 28:37.375
It's entirely duplicitous.
Think about it.

28:37.382 --> 28:40.044
Why would you risk your relationship with Halley

28:40.052 --> 28:42.008
just to search for some pipe dream?

28:42.012 --> 28:43.252
Just hear me out, man.

28:44.932 --> 28:46.672
I'm sure that I love Halley, all right?

28:46.683 --> 28:48.514
And maybe every time
you fall in love with somebody,

28:48.518 --> 28:52.102
it's a completely different experience,
so it's a mistake to compare them.

28:52.105 --> 28:53.185
- I get it, but...
- Right.

28:54.691 --> 28:55.680
All right...

28:56.401 --> 28:59.564
It's like Halley is
<i>The Godfather, Part II.</i>

29:00.781 --> 29:01.736
She's what?

29:01.740 --> 29:04.356
<i>Godfather, Part II.</i>
That was an incredible movie.

29:04.368 --> 29:06.575
Might be better than the original.
All right?

29:06.578 --> 29:08.489
But no matter how much you love
<i>The Godfather, Part II,</i>

29:08.497 --> 29:10.112
you still have to see the original

29:10.624 --> 29:13.161
to understand and appreciate
the sequel, don't ya?

29:14.002 --> 29:15.867
Come on. Is it too much to ask
of my oldest friend to help me out?

29:15.879 --> 29:17.415
You already got
the fairy-tale marriage.

29:17.422 --> 29:19.208
I'm the best man.

29:19.216 --> 29:20.752
You work in the biggest newspaper in the world.

29:20.759 --> 29:21.748
- Now, why don't you help me find her?
- Let me tell you something:

29:21.760 --> 29:25.048
Contrary to popular New York myth,
the <i>Times</i> is not omniscient.

29:25.138 --> 29:27.595
I need a last name.
I need a social security number.

29:27.599 --> 29:30.341
- If we find the book...
- It... It's a dead end. You know that.

29:30.352 --> 29:31.762
Unless we search every bookstore in New York.

29:31.770 --> 29:33.260
You did that. Years ago.

29:33.272 --> 29:35.183
- Do you remember?
- Maybe I missed a store.

29:35.190 --> 29:36.771
Maybe somebody bought it and sold it back.

29:36.775 --> 29:39.812
Here's the deal. You know what?
I don't want any part of this.

29:39.820 --> 29:40.935
All right?

29:56.461 --> 29:58.372
Maybe I am just getting cold feet.

29:58.380 --> 30:00.837
I'm telling you right now,
British women do not age well.

30:01.383 --> 30:04.375
You know, I mean, years ago, yes,
she was a luscious treat.

30:04.386 --> 30:06.877
You know, she probably looked like,
you know, Baby Spice.

30:06.888 --> 30:08.549
But now she could look like...

30:10.350 --> 30:12.136
Old Spice.

30:25.449 --> 30:29.442
- It's a great haircut.
- Oh. Thanks.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.820
- Tell me you love me.
- I love you.

30:32.831 --> 30:35.914
- Tell me something romantic.
- Like what?

30:36.376 --> 30:38.367
I don't know. Like...

30:39.504 --> 30:42.746
how I'm the only girl in the entire universe
meant for you.

30:47.346 --> 30:48.836
Oh, my God, the dinner!

30:50.515 --> 30:52.847
By the way, I emptied your closet.

30:52.851 --> 30:54.512
We gotta pack for the honeymoon.

30:54.519 --> 30:56.851
God, I hate this building.

30:56.855 --> 30:59.141
Shut up!

30:59.149 --> 31:01.014
Don't hit it with the thing.

31:02.527 --> 31:03.937
- Jon!
- What?

31:04.488 --> 31:06.570
I'm gonna go yell at the super.

32:02.504 --> 32:04.415
I don't understand why this is going off.

32:04.423 --> 32:06.288
You said last week it would be fine.

32:06.299 --> 32:07.835
- Hey, Jon.
- Hey.

32:07.843 --> 32:10.380
Jesus, this place looks like a disaster area.

32:10.387 --> 32:13.220
- Thanks, Gerald.
- Gerald, it's in here.

32:13.223 --> 32:15.555
I gotta get going. Coming!

33:05.192 --> 33:08.400
Come on! I wanna see!
I wanna see! I wanna see...

33:08.403 --> 33:11.270
I thought you wanted
a round-cut diamond.

33:11.281 --> 33:12.691
Why? When did I say that?

33:12.699 --> 33:15.782
I'm not exactly sure. But, I mean,
when we were younger, I think.

33:15.785 --> 33:19.243
Oh, God. When I was younger,
I was gonna marry Boris Becker, wasn't I?

33:19.247 --> 33:21.454
- Hey, guys.
- Hey!

33:21.458 --> 33:23.073
- What did you think?
- Well, I mean...

33:23.084 --> 33:25.746
Was that last song really inspired by my sister?

33:25.754 --> 33:27.710
Every artist needs his muse.

33:27.714 --> 33:30.456
- Who wants to hear the good news?
- Hey, I pay you for the good news.

33:30.467 --> 33:32.458
No. You pay me to keep away
the bad news.

33:32.469 --> 33:34.130
Bring it on.

33:34.137 --> 33:37.129
Lars' dates in Stockholm sold out
in eight hours.

33:37.140 --> 33:38.846
Wow!

33:38.850 --> 33:40.511
That means we're gonna have to
add some more shows.

33:40.519 --> 33:42.055
So we'll bump Paris and then we'll...

33:42.062 --> 33:45.145
Sorry. Um, I don't wanna
spoil anyone's party,

33:45.148 --> 33:47.355
but Lars and I have already set the dates
for our honeymoon and our wedding,

33:47.359 --> 33:50.021
and I've told my patients when I'm going.

33:50.028 --> 33:53.361
Well, baby, your patients can do
without you for a couple weeks.

33:53.365 --> 33:54.445
He's right, Sara. I mean,

33:54.449 --> 33:56.815
a couple of extra weeks in Europe
aren't gonna kill you.

33:56.826 --> 33:58.942
Caroline's just pushing you to stay longer

33:58.954 --> 34:01.570
'cause she wants us
to house-sit for you guys.

34:01.790 --> 34:04.657
Yeah, thank you. I was going to ask her
when she was drunk.

34:04.668 --> 34:07.250
- Actually, that's a great idea.
- Yeah?

34:07.254 --> 34:11.964
Yes! Come on, Kip. Let's get out of here
before Sara changes Lars' mind.

34:13.802 --> 34:16.168
- I said something wrong?
- No, it's...

34:16.179 --> 34:20.263
I've just got a very detailed schedule,
and my patients are important too.

34:20.266 --> 34:22.178
I don't like changing the dates
at the last minute.

34:22.185 --> 34:23.049
You know what I mean?

34:23.061 --> 34:24.050
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

34:24.062 --> 34:27.304
But I really need you to approve
these T-shirt designs for Australia.

34:27.315 --> 34:28.929
- Oh, no problem.
- You don't mind, do you?

34:28.942 --> 34:30.728
- Can we do this later?
- Yeah.

34:30.735 --> 34:32.145
She don't mind.

35:18.783 --> 35:21.445
That's chamomile for you ladies.
Nice and hot.

35:21.453 --> 35:22.613
- Very good.
- But, Eve...

35:22.621 --> 35:25.158
Sara, it was a movie poster.
It's no big deal.

35:25.165 --> 35:27.121
It's peculiar though, right?
